    Introduction

    Welcome to the Unsolved API. (Version 1)

    Keys

    • api-key
    • access_token
    • refresh_token

    Header

    • "Header: x-api-key: api-key" is a required header to access all apis

    Registration

    Signup

    This endpoint is to register user. Generates otp and sends otp automatically

    URL: "localhost:3000/api/v1/registrations/"
METHOD: POST

    The request JSON structure:

    {
   "user" : {
        "first_name": "abcd",
        "last_name": "xyz",
        "email": "abcd@gmail.com",
        "country_code": "+91",
        "phone": "9988776655",
        "password": "abcd",
        "terms_of_service": true
   },
   "device_token": "pqrst"
}

    The response JSON structure

    {
    "access_token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJ1c2VyX2lkIjoxLCJleHAiOjE2Mjg3NjEzNTR9.uk_g3M_W8fV-Ov--plaLGUDeI8LDPaT-iwdmJnbX4GE",
    "refresh_token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJ1c2VyX3Rva2VuIjoieDZRNnZiNkJuNG80U2lCTGgxajNWUlJOIiwiZXhwIjoxNjYwMjk3Mjk0fQ.Hc_oMp0LvQ-BuUGi4SFyT9eNy59WdftdKOooTXGjxJw"
}

    HTTP Request

    POST localhost:3000/api/v1/registrations/

    Data Parameters

    Parameter Required Value Description
    first_name true String First name of user
    last_name true String Last name of user
    country_code true String Phone country code
    phone true String Phone number of the user
    email true String Email of user
    password true String Password of the user
    terms_of_service true boolean required true for registration
    device_token true String Device token of the mobile. Won't raise error if missing
    user parameters should be structured under key 'user'

    Verify Otp

    This endpoint is to verify otp.

    URL: "localhost:3000/api/v1/registrations/verify_otp"
METHOD: POST
HEADER: Authorization: Bearer access_token

    The request JSON structure:

    {
    "otp": "1234"
}

    The response JSON structure

    {
    "success": true,
    "msg": "otp verified"
}

    HTTP Request

    POST localhost:3000/api/v1/registrations/verify_otp

    HTTP Header

    Authorization: Bearer access_token

    Data Parameters

    Parameter Required Value Description
    otp true String Otp string

    Resend Otp

    This endpoint is to resend otp.

    URL: "localhost:3000/api/v1/registrations/resend_otp"
METHOD: POST
HEADER: Authorization: Bearer access_token

    The response JSON structure

    {
    "success": true,
    "msg": "otp resent"
}

    HTTP Request

    POST localhost:3000/api/v1/registrations/resend_otp

    HTTP Header

    Authorization: Bearer access_token

    Authentication

    Signin

    This endpoint signs in user.

    URL: "localhost:3000/api/v1/sessions/"
METHOD: POST

    The request JSON structure:

    {

    "email": "abcd@gmail.com",
    "password": "abcd",
    "device_token": "pqrst"

}

    The response JSON structure

    {
    "access_token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJ1c2VyX2lkIjoxLCJleHAiOjE2Mjg3NjQ5OTR9.Fy9eDDQCnRVdqk7ylPl_at-Pjo8NLsfYA6Oe_hHYmUo",
    "refresh_token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJsel9reV81eDgiOiJlQm1ud3o4Z3p3a3FwMkpteEVYeHVyTGUiLCJleHAiOjE2NjAzMDA5MzR9.3oS42Z1_9_Qp0kraQUms7lsJq3jbzt_UL119tnHyQyk"
}

    HTTP Request

    POST localhost:3000/api/v1/sessions/

    Data Parameters

    Parameter Required Value Description
    email true String Email of user
    password true String Password of the user
    device_token true String Device token of the mobile. Won't raise error if missing
    You must replace api-key with your API key.

    New access token

    This endpoint signs in user.

    URL: "localhost:3000/api/v1/sessions/refresh"
METHOD: GET
HEADER: Authorization: Bearer refresh_token

    The response JSON structure

    {
    "access_token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJ1c2VyX2lkIjoxLCJleHAiOjE2Mjg3NjQ5OTR9.Fy9eDDQCnRVdqk7ylPl_at-Pjo8NLsfYA6Oe_hHYmUo",
    "refresh_token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJsel9reV81eDgiOiJlQm1ud3o4Z3p3a3FwMkpteEVYeHVyTGUiLCJleHAiOjE2NjAzMDA5MzR9.3oS42Z1_9_Qp0kraQUms7lsJq3jbzt_UL119tnHyQyk"
}

    HTTP Request

    GET localhost:3000/api/v1/sessions/refresh

    HTTP Header

    Authorization: Bearer refresh_token

    Logout

    This endpoint logs out the user.

    URL: "localhost:3000/api/v1/sessions"
METHOD: DELETE
HEADER: Authorization: Bearer refresh_token

    The request JSON structure:

    {
    "device_token": "pqrst"
}

    HTTP Request

    DELETE localhost:3000/api/v1/sessions/

    HTTP Header

    Authorization: Bearer access_token

    Data Parameters

    Parameter Required Value Description
    device_token true String Device token of the mobile. Won't raise error if missing

    Reset Password

    Password Reset

    This endpoint sends password reset email with otp to the user.

    URL: "localhost:3000/api/v1/password_reset"
METHOD: POST

    The request JSON structure:

    {
    "email": "allendavis2911@gmail.com"
}

    HTTP Request

    POST localhost:3000/api/v1/password_reset/

    Data Parameters

    Parameter Required Value Description
    email true String Email of the user

    Verify Otp

    This endpoint verifies password reset otp.

    URL: "localhost:3000/api/v1/password_reset/verify_otp"
METHOD: POST

    The request JSON structure:

    {
    "email": "allendavis2911@gmail.com",
    "otp": "1234"
}

    HTTP Request

    POST localhost:3000/api/v1/password_reset/verify_otp

    Data Parameters

    Parameter Required Value Description
    email true String Email of the user
    otp true String Otp entered by the user

    Resend Reset Otp

    This endpoint resends user password reset otp.

    URL: "localhost:3000/api/v1/password_reset/resend_reset_otp"
METHOD: POST

    The request JSON structure:

    {
    "email": "allendavis2911@gmail.com",
}

    HTTP Request

    POST localhost:3000/api/v1/password_reset/resend_reset_otp

    Data Parameters

    Parameter Required Value Description
    email true String Email of the user

    Users

METHOD: GET
HEADER: Authorization: Bearer access_token

}

    HTTP Request

    GET localhost:3000/api/v1/sessions/<ID>

    HTTP Header

    Authorization: Bearer access_token

    URL Parameters

    Parameter Required Value Description
    ID true Integer ID of the user

    Update User

    This endpoint update user data. current user should be same as the user id in url

    URL: "localhost:3000/api/v1/users/1"
METHOD: PATCH
HEADER: Authorization: Bearer access_token

    The request JSON structure:

    {
    "user": {
        "first_name":"Allen",
        "last_name":"Davis",
        "phone": "9988776655",
        "country_code": "+91",
        "all_tags": ["ror", "javascript"],
        "all_industry_tags": ["it", "computer-science"],
        "avatar": file,
        "banner_image": file,
        "user_profile_attributes": {
            "id": 4,
            "about": "Lorem Ipsum is simply dummy text of the printing and typesetting industry. Lorem Ipsum has been the industry's standard dummy text ever since the 1500s, when an unknown printer took a galley of type and scrambled it to make a type specimen book.",
            "headline": "It is a long established fact that a reader will be distracted by the readable content of a page when looking at its layout",
            "linkedin": "https://www.linkedin.com/allendavis",
            "twitter": "https://www.twitter.com/allendavis",
            "github": "https://www.github.com/allendavis",
            "behance": "https://www.behance.com/allendavis",
            "website": "https://www.allendavis.com/",
            "blog": "https://www.blog.com/allendavis",
            "full_time_work_start_year": "2020"
        }
    }
}

    The response JSON structure

    {
    "id": 1,
    "first_name": "Allen",
    "last_name": "Davis",
    "name": "Allen Davis",
    "slug": "allen-davis",
    "avatar": "http://localhost:3000/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBIQT09IiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--d0a8cd460e689d2cc799bacf15b1a9c6bdf697bc/1616072204090.jpg",
    "banner_image": "http://localhost:3000/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBIUT09IiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--ea49f94c6260f340fe4b87fe725a4369a8e75b4e/highres-Pentax-K-1-with-70-200mm-lens-20160428_100020_1461842110.jpg",
    "user_profile": {
        "id": 4,
        "about": "Lorem Ipsum is simply dummy text of the printing and typesetting industry. Lorem Ipsum has been the industry's standard dummy text ever since the 1500s, when an unknown printer took a galley of type and scrambled it to make a type specimen book.",
        "headline": "It is a long established fact that a reader will be distracted by the readable content of a page when looking at its layout",

        "github": "https://www.github.com/allendavis",
        "behance": "https://www.behance.com/allendavis"
    }
}

    HTTP Request

    PATCH localhost:3000/api/v1/users/<ID>

    HTTP Header

    Authorization: Bearer access_token

    URL Parameters

    Parameter Required Value Description
    ID true Integer ID of the current user

    User Startups

    This endpoint retrevies all startups user is part of.

    URL: "localhost:3000/api/v1/users/1/founded_startups"
METHOD: GET
HEADER: Authorization: Bearer access_token

    The response JSON structure

    {
    "startups": [
        {
            "id": 3,
            "title": "Oasis Tourism pvt ltd",
            "description": "Lorem Ipsum is simply dummy text of the printing and typesetting industry. Lorem Ipsum has been the industry's standard dummy text ever sinc",
            "image": null,
            "curr_working_here": true
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "title": "Test Company 2",
            "description": "Lorem Ipsum is simply dummy text of the printing and typesetting industry. Lorem Ipsum has been the industry's standard dummy text ever sinc",

            "curr_working_here": false

    ]
}

    HTTP Request

    GET localhost:3000/api/v1/users/<ID>/founded_startups

    HTTP Header

    Authorization: Bearer access_token

    URL Parameters

    Parameter Required Value Description
    ID true Integer ID of the user

    Reset User Password

    This endpoint resets user password.

    URL: "localhost:3000/api/v1/users/update_password"
METHOD: PATCH

    The request JSON structure:

    {
    "user": {
        "email": "allendavis2911@gmail.com",
        "password": "password@123"
    }
}

    The response JSON structure

    {
    "id": 1,
    "first_name": "Allen",
    "last_name": "Davis",
    "name": "Allen Davis",

    HTTP Request

    POST localhost:3000/api/v1/accounts

    HTTP Header

    Authorization: Bearer access_token

    DATA Parameters

    Parameter Value Description
    ID Integer ID of account

    Join account

    current user will join this account.

    Url:

    URL: "localhost:3000/api/v1/accounts/1/join_account"
METHOD: POST
HEADER: "Authorization: Bearer access_token"

    The response JSON structure

    {
    "success": true,
    "msg": "Successfully joined the network"
}

    HTTP Request

    POST localhost:3000/api/v1/accounts/<ID>/join_account

    HTTP Header

    Authorization: Bearer access_token

    DATA Parameters

    Parameter Value Description
    ID Integer ID of account

    Leave account

    current user will leave this account.

    Url:

    URL: "localhost:3000/api/v1/accounts/1/leave_account"
METHOD: DELETE
HEADER: "Authorization: Bearer access_token"

    The response JSON structure

    {
    "success": true,
    "msg": "Successfully left the network"
}

    HTTP Request

    DELETE localhost:3000/api/v1/accounts/<ID>/leave_account

    HTTP Header

    Authorization: Bearer access_token -(required)

    DATA Parameters

    Parameter Value Description
    ID Integer ID of account

    HTTP Request

    GET localhost:3000/api/v1/accounts/<ID>/feed

    HTTP Header

    Authorization: Bearer access_token

    Filter Options

    GET localhost:3000/api/v1/accounts/<ID>/feed?search=asdf

    DATA Parameters

    Parameter Value Description
    ID Integer ID of account

    Get Account Courses

    This endpoint will get all courses of a particular account.

    Url:

    URL: "localhost:3000/api/v1/accounts/1/courses"
METHOD: GET
HEADER: "Authorization: Bearer access_token"

    The response JSON structure

    {
    "courses": [
        {
            "id": 9,
            "title": "sample 6",
            "description": "adfsdb",
            "duration": null,
            "duration_interval": "Hours",
            "starts_at": null,
            "no_of_seats": null,
            "no_of_enrollments": 0,

    HTTP Request

    GET localhost:3000/api/v1/accounts/categorized_accounts

    HTTP Header

    Authorization: Bearer access_token

    Feed

    Get User Feed

    this endpoint will get all posts from all accounts user is part of.

    Url:

    URL: "localhost:3000/api/v1/feed"
METHOD: GET
HEADER: "Authorization: Bearer access_token"

    CoursePost
    StartupPost

    Discussion

    Create Post

    This endpoint will create post in an account.

    URL: "localhost:3000/api/v1/posts"
METHOD: POST
HEADER: "Authorization: Bearer access_token"

    The request JSON structure (link url example):

    {
    "post": {
        "body": "link url: test api",
        "video_url": "",
        "link_url": "https://uxdesign.cc/the-real-reason-facebook-is-changing-its-name-to-meta-what-you-must-know-from-facebooks-2021-e8f12cdc797c",
        "link_url_site": "Medium",
        "link_url_title": "The real reason Facebook is changing its name to Meta",
        "link_url_description": "What you must know from Facebooks 2021 AR/VR conference.",
        "link_url_image": "https://miro.medium.com/max/1200/1*88U0EI-rnnQIuIkTFIC1cQ.png"
        // "images": [],
        // "pinned": false,
        // "pinned_in_startup_feed": false,
        // "visible_on_feed": true,
        // "redirect_url": "",
        // "startup_id": null

    },
    "account_id": 1
}

    The request JSON structure (video url example):

    {
    "post": {
        "body": "link url: test api",
        "video_url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pfeyxy7wVXg"
        // "link_url": "https://uxdesign.cc/the-real-reason-facebook-is-changing-its-name-to-meta-what-you-must-know-from-facebooks-2021-e8f12cdc797c",
        // "link_url_site": "Medium",
        // "link_url_title": "The real reason Facebook is changing its name to Meta",
        // "link_url_description": "What you must know from Facebooks 2021 AR/VR conference.",
        // "link_url_image": "https://miro.medium.com/max/1200/1*88U0EI-rnnQIuIkTFIC1cQ.png"
        // "images": [],

    HTTP Request

    DELETE localhost:3000/api/v1/comments/<ID>

    HTTP Header

    Authorization: Bearer access_token - (required)

    HTTP Header

    • If comment has nested comments than the comment doesn't get deleted, the comment data and the user data becomes null.
    • If comment doesn't have nested comment than the comment gets deleted.

    DATA Parameters

    Parameter Value Description
    ID Integer ID of the comment

    Delete Comment file

    this endpoint will delete a comment file.

    URL: "localhost:3000/api/v1/comments/47/destroy_file/67"
METHOD: DELETE
HEADER: "Authorization: Bearer access_token"

    The response JSON structure

    {
    "success": "true",
    "msg": "File was successfully deleted"
}

    HTTP Request

    DELETE localhost:3000/api/v1/comments/<ID>/destroy_file/<FILE_ID>

    HTTP Header

    Authorization: Bearer access_token

    DATA Parameters

    Parameter Value Description
    ID Integer ID of the comment
    FILE_ID Integer ID of the file

    GET http://localhost:3000/courses/<ID>

    Parameter Description
    ID The ID of the course

    This endpoint creates a course.

    URL:  "http://localhost:3000/api/courses"

    HTTP Request

    POST http://localhost:3000/courses

    HTTP Header

    Authorization: Bearer access_token

    DATA Parameters

    Parameter Type Value required Description
    account_id Integer ID true ID of the account
    commit String ["save", draft] true 'save' will update/create & publish the course & 'draft' will save update/create & save the course as draft
    title String - true title of the course
    description String - true description of the course
    level String ['Beginner', 'Intermediate', 'Advanced'] optional level of the course
    preview_video_url String - optional Preview Video - Add a Youtube URL(2 min)
    currency String ["INR"] required default will be inr
    course_price Float - optional, * required if discounted price exists price of the course
    discounted_price Float - optional Discounted price of the course
    duration Integer - optional duration of the course
    duration_interval String ['Minutes', 'Hours', 'Days', 'Weeks', 'Months', 'Years'] optional duration of the course, default is 'Hours'
    course_session_type String ['live', 'recorded', 'live_recorded'] optional Session type of the course
    community String ["0","1"] optional Methodology of course
    peer_review String ["0","1"] optional Methodology of course
    live_q_and_a String ["0","1"] optional Methodology of course
    live_projects String ["0","1"] optional Methodology of course
    guest_lectures String ["0","1"] optional Methodology of course
    case_studies String ["0","1"] optional Methodology of course
    templates String ["0","1"] optional Methodology of course
    certificate String ["0","1"] optional Methodology of course
    instructor_review String - optional, * required if instructor_review_price exists -
    instructor_review_price Float - optional Review Price
    one_on_one_consultation String - optional, * required if instructor_review_price exists -
    one_on_one_consultation_price Float - optional 1-on-1 consultation Price
    on_demand Boolean - optional Preview
    all_tags Array - optional All Categories
    all_target_group_tags Array - optional Who is this for

    HTTP Request

    GET http://localhost:3000/courses/<ID>/course_sessions

    HTTP Header

    Authorization: Bearer access_token

    URL Parameters

    Parameter Description
    ID The ID of the course

    Get course review

    This endpoint retrevies course review by current user.

    URL:  "http://localhost:3000/api/courses/7/course_review?account_id=1"
METHOD: GET
HEADER: "Authorization: Bearer access_token"

    The response JSON structure

    {
    "id": 1,
    "review": "This course is awsome"
}

    HTTP Request

    GET http://localhost:3000/courses/<ID>/course_review?account_id=1

    HTTP Header

    Authorization: Bearer access_token

    URL Parameters

    Parameter Description
    ID The ID of the course

But in certain circumstances and owing to the claims of duty or the obligations of business it will frequently occur that pleasures have to be repudiated and annoyances accepted.     Course Reviews

    Create course review

    This endpoint creates a review for the course.

    URL:  "localhost:3000/api/v1/courses/11/course_reviews"
METHOD: POST
HEADER: "Authorization: Bearer access_token"

    The request JSON structure

    {
    "course_review": {
        "review": "Test review"
    }
}

    The response JSON structure

    {
    "id": 3,
    "review": "Test review"
}

    HTTP Request

    POST http://localhost:3000/courses/<COURSE_ID>/course_reviews

    HTTP Header

    Authorization: Bearer access_token

    URL Parameters

    Parameter Description
    COURSE_ID The ID of the course session

    Data Parameters

    Parameter Description
    account_id The ID of the account

    Update course review

    This endpoint updates a review for the course.

    URL:  "localhost:3000/api/v1/courses/11/course_reviews/3"
METHOD: PATCH
HEADER: "Authorization: Bearer access_token"

    The request JSON structure

    {
    "course_review": {
        "review": "Test review"
    }, 
    "account_id": 1
}

    The response JSON structure

    {
    "id": 3,
    "review": "Test review"
}

    HTTP Request

    PATCH http://localhost:3000/courses/<COURSE_ID>/course_reviews/<COURSE_REVIEW_ID>

    HTTP Header

    Authorization: Bearer access_token

    URL Parameters

    Parameter Description
    COURSE_ID The ID of the course session
    COURSE_REVIEW_ID ID of the course review

    This endpoint creates a specific job.

    HTTP Request

    POST https://localhost:3000/api/v1/jobs

    Data parameters

    Parameter Value Description
    title String Title of the job
    company_name String Name of the company hiring
    website String Website of the company hiring
    description String Description of the job
    account_id Integer The Network id under which the job post is created
    global Boolean Default is false, If set to true, It will add job to global repo
    parameters should be structured under key 'job'

    Update a job

    URL: "http://localhost:3000/api/jobs/1"
METHOD: PATCH
HEADER: "Authorization: Bearer access_token"

    The request JSON structure:

    {
    "job": {
        "title":"React Native Developer (3+ years) Edit",
        "company_name":"Unsolved Network",
        "website":"www.unsolved.network",
        "description":"Just description",
        "global":true
    }
}

    The response JSON structure

    {
    "id": 2,
    "user": {
        "id": 1,
        "name": "Allen davis2911"
    },
    "title":"React Native Developer (3+ years) Edit",
    "company_name":"Unsolved Network",
    "website":"www.unsolved.network",
    "description":"Just description",   
    "global": true,
    "slug": "react-native-developer-3-years-of-experience",
    "published_at": "2021-08-03T08:46:16.070Z",
    "created_at": "2021-08-03T08:46:16.176Z"
}

    This endpoint updates a specific job.

    HTTP Request

    PATCH https://localhost:3000/api/v1/jobs/<ID>

    URL Parameters

    Parameter Description
    ID The ID of the job

    Data parameters

    Parameter Value Description
    title String Title of the job
    company_name String Name of the company hiring
    website String Website of the company hiring
    description String Description of the job
    account_id Integer The Network id under which the job post is created
    global Boolean Default is false, If set to true, It will add job to global repo
    parameters should be structured under key 'job'

    Add job to Network

    URL: "http://localhost:3000/api/jobs/1/add_to_network"
METHOD: POST
HEADER: "Authorization: Bearer access_token"

    The response JSON structure

    {
    "id": 2,
    "user": {
        "id": 1,
        "name": "Allen davis2911"
    },
    "title":"React Native Developer (3+ years) Edit",
    "company_name":"Unsolved Network",
    "website":"www.unsolved.network",
    "description":"Just description",   
    "global": true,
    "slug": "react-native-developer-3-years-of-experience",
    "published_at": "2021-08-03T08:46:16.070Z",
    "created_at": "2021-08-03T08:46:16.176Z"
}

    This endpoint adds global job to current network.

    HTTP Request

    POST https://localhost:3000/api/v1/jobs/<ID>/add_to_network

    URL Parameters

    Parameter Description
    ID The ID of the job

    Remove job from network

    URL: "http://localhost:3000/api/jobs/1/remove_from_network"
METHOD: DELETE
HEADER: "Authorization: Bearer access_token"

    The response JSON structure

    {
    "success": true,
    "msg": "successfully removed from network"
}
    • This endpoint removes job to current network.
    • If global job, then job is removed from all networks and deleted from db
    • If private job, then its deleted from db

    HTTP Request

    DELETE https://localhost:3000/api/v1/jobs/<ID>/remove_from_network

    URL Parameters

    Parameter Description
    ID The ID of the job
